    <link href="http://www.samhamilton.co.uk/blog/2009/05/23/f1-the-world-gone-mad/"/>
    <updated>2009-05-23T06:53:00+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://www.samhamilton.co.uk/blog/2009/05/23/f1-the-world-gone-mad</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>So I went on holiday just before the Spanish GP and in the matter of two weeks the F1 world has gone bonkers, we have had:</p>

<ul>
<li><p><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/sport2/hi/motorsport/formula_one/8058903.stm">Ferrari take the F1 to court</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/sport2/hi/motorsport/formula_one/8060335.stm"> Alonso</a> &amp; <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/sport2/hi/motorsport/formula_one/8041530.stm">Rikkonen</a> thinking about leaving</p></li>
<li><p><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/sport2/hi/motorsport/formula_one/8057339.stm">Massa nearly gets into the big points but runs out of petrol</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/sport2/hi/motorsport/formula_one/8041568.stm">Button wins his third
</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/sport2/hi/motorsport/formula_one/8041690.stm">Aston Martin</a> &amp; <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/sport2/hi/motorsport/formula_one/8050970.stm">Litespeed</a> ponders a return</p></li>
<li><p><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/2/hi/uk_news/england/8049479.stm">Donington is &ldquo;safe&rdquo;</a></p></li>
</ul>


<p>And that is just the most interesting ones!</p>
]]></content>
